            "Type": 1,
            "Data": "The Apollo 8 mission profile is a lunar mission where the CSM is inserted into orbit using the Saturn V. The SIV-B stage is re-ignited for the TLI burn before being separated. The CSM continues the journey to the moon. Two LOI burns are used to insert the craft into lunar orbit. 10 lunar orbit revolutions are completed before returning to Earth.\r\n\r\nThe following burns are scheduled:\r\n1) TLI\r\n2) LOI-1\r\n3) LOI-2\r\n4) TEI\r\n\r\nSee below for more details related to the burns. It is not expected to perform any of the MCC burns.\r\n\r\n",
